TITLE: Testing a Greeter Class with PHPUnit
DESCRIPTION: A PHPUnit test class that demonstrates basic testing conventions for the Greeter class, asserting that the greet method returns the expected string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit-documentation-english/blob/12.0/src/writing-tests-for-phpunit.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

use PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes\Test;
use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;

final class GreeterTest extends TestCase
{
    #[Test]
    public function greetReturnsHelloName(): void
    {
        $greeter = new Greeter\Greeter;

        $greeting = $greeter->greet('Jane');

        $this->assertSame('Hello, Jane!', $greeting);
    }
}
```

