TITLE: Marking Tests as Incomplete in PHPUnit
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to mark a test as incomplete using markTestIncomplete() to indicate tests that are not yet fully implemented or ready for execution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit-documentation-english/blob/12.0/src/writing-tests-for-phpunit.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;

final class WorkInProgressTest extends TestCase
{
    public function testSomething(): void
    {
        // Optional: Test anything here, if you want.
        $this->assertTrue(true);

        // Stop here and mark this test as incomplete.
        $this->markTestIncomplete(
            'This test has not been implemented yet.'
        );
    }
}
```

