TITLE: Stubbing a Method to Return an Argument in PHPUnit
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use willReturnArgument() to make a stubbed method return one of its arguments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit-documentation-english/blob/12.0/src/test-doubles.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
public function testReturnArgumentStub(): void
{
    $stub = $this->createStub(SomeClass::class);

    $stub->method('doSomething')
         ->willReturnArgument(0);

    $this->assertSame('foo', $stub->doSomething('foo'));
    $this->assertSame('bar', $stub->doSomething('bar'));
}
```

