TITLE: Testing Object Equality in PHPUnit
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use assertObjectEquals() to compare Value Objects using their equals() method. Includes example with Email value object implementation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit-documentation-english/blob/12.0/src/assertions.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php declare(strict_types=1);
use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;

final class ObjectEqualsTest extends TestCase
{
    public function testEmailObjects(): void
    {
        $expected = new Email('user@example.org');
        $actual   = new Email('user@example.org');

        $this->assertObjectEquals($expected, $actual);
    }
}
```

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php declare(strict_types=1);
final class Email
{
    private string $email;

    public function __construct(string $email)
    {
        $this->email = $email;
    }

    public function equals(self $other): bool
    {
        return $this->email === $other->email;
    }
}
```

