TITLE: Stubbing a Method Call in PHPUnit
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a test stub for Dependency and configure it to return a fixed value when doSomething() is called.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit-documentation-english/blob/12.0/src/test-doubles.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
public function testStub(): void
{
    // Create a stub for the Dependency class.
    $stub = $this->createStub(Dependency::class);

    // Configure the stub.
    $stub->method('doSomething')
         ->willReturn('foo');

    // Create a new instance of SomeClass and inject the stub
    $object = new SomeClass($stub);

    // Now $object->doSomething() will return 'foo'
    $this->assertSame('foo', $object->doSomething());
}
```

