TITLE: Defining Test Class for Error Handling in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This PHP class defines unit tests that trigger deprecation warnings from both first-party and third-party code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit-documentation-english/blob/12.0/src/error-handling.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

namespace example;

use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;

final class FirstPartyClassTest extends TestCase
{
    public function testOne(): void
    {
        $object = new FirstPartyClass;
        $object->deprecatedMethod();

        $this->assertTrue(true);
    }

    public function testTwo(): void
    {
        $object = new \ThirdPartyClass;
        $object->deprecatedMethod();

        $this->assertTrue(true);
    }
}
```

